## Decoding SKY130 Library Naming Convention

I studied the naming convention used in the SKY130 standard cell library.

Example:

```text
sky130_fd_sc_hd__tt_025C_1v80
```

### Meaning

| Term   | Description               |
| ------ | ------------------------- |
| sky130 | SkyWater 130nm technology |
| fd     | Foundry design            |
| sc     | Standard cells            |
| hd     | High-density library      |
| tt     | Typical process corner    |
| 025C   | Temperature = 25°C        |
| 1v80   | Supply voltage = 1.8V     |

This naming convention indicates the exact operating conditions under which the library has been characterized.

